      <hedline>
        <hl1>Mouse Manipulations</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Arnie Huberman letter, responding to Oct 1 article, says it is unnecessary to purchase cleaning kit for computer mouse; describes how he regularly cleans his mouse</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>The article ''Behold the Lowly Mouse: Clever Technology Close at Hand'' (Oct. 1) suggests that users pay approximately $6 for a mouse cleaning kit. Not necessary. On a regular basis, I open the mouse to access the ball, and wipe it clean with a cloth dipped in vodka. The alcohol cleans the mouse, and at a fraction of the cost. The only problem -- I often come home and find the mouse pointing to the liquor cabinet!</p>
        <p>ARNIE HUBERMAN  New York, Oct. 1, 1998</p>
      </block>
